page.title: 14Ecology: Animals (1)
page.content:
Frogs and grass-snakes are rare. The commonest butterflies are tortoiseshell, peacock, red admiral and white cabbage. Ringlets also occur. Earthworms abound.
Roach, dace and chub come up Bottisham lode to spawn. Swaffham lode contains bream, pike, and some escaped trout. Eels occur in both lodes, as the closed lock gates of Swaffham do not present a barrier to them.
Birds abound in the fen. Herons, moorhens, mute swans, reedbuntings, reed and sedge warblers are common along the watercourses. Kingfisher, common snipe and tufted duck also occur there. Coot are absent.
